jy.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/DuPb3z1.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Uc2beSB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tx5jQSv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I may not be an old woman, but of my 6 cats, one was a gift, one I rescued from a drug house, two were abandoned after being left in my care, 1 was a feral cat one of the others brought home, and the latest was abandoned by a former tenant of my landlord's. He figured I knew something about cats.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/vZfVpq8</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Swiggy1957]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>“Was my position eliminated or not?”</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/eDEwVSn</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dHUjV0I.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Front page EDIT: Yay! Front Page! I just wanted to add that I’ve never worked in food service but after watching the movie ‘Waiting…’ and more recently the Hulu series ‘Bear’ I have a new found respect for everyone that works in the restaurant industry.

I’ve always known it’s difficult for all restaurant staff but was clueless as to how much work really goes into running a restaurant. Especially through the pandemic. So if you are in that line of work, hats off to you and thanks for all you do!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/eDEwVSn</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[dorenavant]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Who reads beyond the headline nowadays?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/xuyVfvf</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Ooy3C1O.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/xuyVfvf</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[PineappleIsDeliciousOnPizzaFightMe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>It's Never Too Late</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/VafpeNT</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/g0bG1u3.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>– At age 23, Tina Fey was working at a YMCA.

– At age 23, Oprah was fired from her first reporting job.

– At age 24, Stephen King was working as a janitor and living in a trailer.

– At age 27, Vincent Van Gogh failed as a missionary and decided to go to art school.

– At age 28, J.K. Rowling was a suicidal single parent living on welfare.

– At age 28, Wayne Coyne (from The Flaming Lips) was a fry cook.

– At age 30, Harrison Ford was a carpenter.

– At age 30, Martha Stewart was a stockbroker.

– At age 37, Ang Lee was a stay-at-home-dad working odd jobs.

– Julia Child released her first cookbook at age 49.

– Vera Wang failed to make the Olympic figure skating team, didn’t get the Editor-in-Chief position at Vogue, and designed her first dress at age 40.

– Stan Lee didn’t release his first big comic book until he was 38.

– Alan Rickman gave up his graphic design career to pursue acting at age 42.

– Samuel L. Jackson didn’t get his first major movie role until he was 41.

– Morgan Freeman landed his first MAJOR movie role at age 52.

– Kathryn Bigelow only reached international success when she made The Hurt Locker at age 57.

– Grandma Moses didn’t begin her painting career until age 76.

– Louise Bourgeois wasn’t featured in the Museum of Modern Art until she was 71.

At 37 I was on parole after a 3rd DUI and decided to finally start college. At 47, I was a licensed mental health counselor, working in Hawaii, with my own private practice.

It's not too late.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/VafpeNT</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SillyPhilosopher]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>What kind of witchery is this?!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/43LhUSd</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hYo7TYx.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/43LhUSd</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[IdontEatBooty]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Ten amazing movies you might not have seen!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/nCgPhaM</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/v79z1IF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Layer Cake

A successful cocaine dealer gets two tough assignments from his boss on the eve of his planned early retirement.  

http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0375912/</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/M5Ns8O9.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Sunshine 

50 years into the future, the Sun begins to die, and Earth is dying as a result. A team of astronauts are sent to revive the Sun - but the mission fails. Seven years later, a new team are sent to finish the mission as they are Earth's last hope.  

http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0448134/</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/thfPCQG.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The Fountain 

Spanning three parallel stories over a millennium, 'The Fountain' is a story of love, death, spirituality, and the fragility of our existence in this world.  

http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0414993/</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/QMX3YIX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tucker and Dale vs Evil 

Two lovable West Virginian hillbillies, are headed to their "fixer-upper" vacation cabin to drink some beer, do some fishin', and have a good time. But when they run into a group of preppy college kids who assume from their looks that they must be in-bred, chainsaw wielding killers, Tucker & Dale's vacation takes a bloody & hilarious turn for the worse.  

http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1465522/</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NQ3MJJH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Unthinkable

